#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Summarize a directory of ``iadplus`` reports.

``iadsum`` searches a directory tree for reports created by ``iadplus``, finds
the matching ``.txt`` output files, and builds a summary report with overlaid
plots for measured reflection/transmission and derived optical properties. It is
useful after running ``iadplus`` on a group of related experiments, because the
generated summary shows how absorption, scattering, anisotropy, albedo, and
optical thickness compare across files.

The script expects each discovered ``.ipynb``, ``.html``, or ``.pdf`` report to
have a sibling ``.txt`` file with the standard ``iad`` tabular output. The
summary is written to a ``summary`` subdirectory inside the requested directory.
By default, the summary format matches the generated report type that was found.

Examples:
    Summarize all ``iadplus`` reports below a test directory::

        ./iadsum tests/rxt/1_sphere

    Summarize reports produced in the current directory tree::

        ./iadsum .
"""

